<div class="mb-requirement-container">
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-13829">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> </span>
      <b
        >NOTE: Stamp and coin collecting are excluded from eligibility for this
        merit badge.<br />Scouts must remember to follow the Leave No Trace
        Seven Principles and the Outdoor Code while on field trips and when
        collecting specimens. Make sure you have permission of the land manager
        prior to taking any samples for your collection. Collecting is
        prohibited in most National and State Parks. Pictures or sketches may
        suffice for a collection and limit impacted disturbances.
      </b>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14076">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> </span>
      <b>NOTE: </b> The official merit badge pamphlets are now free and
      downloadable
      <a
        href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/Merit_Badge_ReqandRes/Pamphlets/Collections.pdf"
        target="_blank"
        >HERE</a
      >
      or can be purchased at the
      <a href="https://www.scoutshop.org/" target="_blank ">Scout Shop.</a>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-9427">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 1. </span>
      Prepare a short written report or outline for your counselor, giving a
      detailed description of your collection, including a short history, why
      you enjoy your collection, and what you have learned from collecting. Be
      sure to include why you chose that particular type of
      collection/collecting method. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/G09aIKMBNhE?si=L6cgpArtfAHD3KjX" target="_blank"
        >The Invention of Collecting (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://icebreakerideas.com/things-to-collect/" target="_blank"
        >246 Cool Things to Collect (Collection Ideas) (website)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/FtaG6XgemUY" target="_blank"
        >Meet Reece, King of the Fans | My Kid's Obsession (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-9428">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 2. </span>
      Explain the growth and development of your collection. <br /><i
        >Resources:</i
      >
      <a href="https://youtu.be/dPnsVmEk3Y4?si=iNIEfkPYFgNyptS9" target="_blank"
        >Collecting Tips 101: Tip #4 Do Your Research (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/rGLfkhaTts4?si=Fo0axri8RXK2S4P8" target="_blank"
        >Collecting Tips 101: Tip #86 Be Unique (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/cOleElanH6w?si=VHZW9zBn0hCuBhvj" target="_blank"
        >Collecting Tips 101: Tip #2 Budget Your Money (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/fB7j8OZk4f0?si=Xot--xUEe_KhfoLT" target="_blank"
        >Collecting Tips 101: Tip #27 Leave Room to Grow (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-9412">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 3. </span>
      Demonstrate your knowledge of preserving and displaying your collection.
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-9412 mb-requirement-id-9413">
        (a) Explain the precautions you need to take to preserve your
        collection, including handling, cleaning, and storage. <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://www.homeaswemakeit.com/20-best-ways-to-store-preserve-vintage-collectibles-for-long-term-value/"
          target="_blank"
          >20 Best Ways to Store &amp; Preserve Vintage Collectibles for
          Long-Term Value (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/1_QFgGbywAc?si=w8wSCQq4ZRex1n0d"
          target="_blank"
          >Collecting Tips 101: Tip #61 You Shalt Dust? (General Cleaning)
          (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/e-5c_DcByWU?si=vKBIDpOrCG5_bkGZ"
          target="_blank"
          >Collecting Tips 101: Tip #25 Where to Keep a Collection (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/Ck5yO9gg1uc?si=eYQvVoeUNfuN26sE"
          target="_blank"
          >Collecting Tips 101: Tip #20 Stay Away From Sunlight (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/shorts/C2-ZPL3jRHU" target="_blank"
          >3 Ways to Store and Organize Your Squishmallows (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-9412 mb-requirement-id-9414">
        (b) Explain how best to display your collection, keeping in mind
        preserving as discussed above. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/VRehA_4XJcY?si=jt-ATiVtwR9iFq_I"
          target="_blank"
          >5 TIPS to Display your Collection LIKE A PRO --- Props, Statues, Star
          Wars &amp; more (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/vveS2xB97b8?si=VoqVo1IMUEBQTVlk"
          target="_blank"
          >How To Display Your Collection Like a PRO (As a Broke College
          Student) (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/xfFWEpkfTl8" target="_blank"
          >How to Display Squishmellows (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-9412 mb-requirement-id-9415">
        (c) Explain to your counselor the events available for a hobbyist of
        this collection, including shows, seminars, conventions, contests, and
        museum programs and exhibits. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://whichmuseum.com/" target="_blank">Museums (website)</a>
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-9412 mb-requirement-id-9433">
        (d) Explain to your counselor how you keep track of your collection.
        Describe your cataloging method. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/shorts/YUn5su6RKDE" target="_blank"
          >How I Keep Track of My 4000+ Dolls! (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/wLAoVbLuur0?si=CTiia13VrYn3jCQA"
          target="_blank"
          >Citizen Collector's Toolkit: How to document your collection
          (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/zLT1aqMgJWs?si=gpAA8ofT-xRp61Ml"
          target="_blank"
          >Collecting Tips 101: Tip #5 Database Your Collection (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/DKOFh-Kyhcs?si=1aXLSq3rDw4iGxVQ"
          target="_blank"
          >How to Organize POKEMON Cards (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-9416">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 4. </span>
      Demonstrate your knowledge of collecting and investing. Discuss with your
      counselor: <br /><i>Resources:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/ZSZXXjrWMf0" target="_blank">
        5 Smart Tips for Collecting Pokemon Cards on a Budget (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a
        href="https://www.investopedia.com/articles/basics/06/contemplatingcollectibles.asp"
        target="_blank"
        >Contemplatiing Collectible Investments (website)</a
      >
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-9416 mb-requirement-id-9417">
        (a) How investing and speculation would apply to your collection
        <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.forbes.com/advisor/investing/how-to-invest-in-collectibles/"
          target="_blank"
          >Find Investments to Meet Your Financial Goals (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/j2YLShzE-PU?si=xpubBGs4hFKCMln0"
          target="_blank"
          >Collecting Tips 101: Tip #48 Predicting Rare Games (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-9416 mb-requirement-id-9418">
        (b) What you would look for in purchasing other collections similar to
        yours
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-9416 mb-requirement-id-9419">
        (c) What you would expect in return value if you decided to sell all or
        part of the collection <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.worldcollectorsnet.com/category/whats-it-worth/"
          target="_blank"
          >What's it Worth - Free Antiques &amp; Collectables Price Guide
          (website)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-9420">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 5. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-9420 mb-requirement-id-9421">
        (a) Discuss with your counselor at least 10 terms commonly used to
        describe your collection and be prepared to discuss the definition of
        each. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://page.nomenclature.info/apropos-about.app?lang=en"
          target="_blank"
          >Nomenclature for Museum Cataloging (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-9420 mb-requirement-id-9422">
        (b) Show your counselor any two groups from your collection. Explain how
        you organized your collection and why you chose that method. (Note: if
        your collection is too large to transport and your counselor is unable
        to view your collection directly, photographs should be available to
        share.)
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-9420 mb-requirement-id-9423">
        (c) Explain the monetary value of your collection and where you learned
        about those values. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.liveabout.com/how-to-find-the-value-of-an-item-780265"
          target="_blank"
          >How to Find Out What It's Worth (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://www.lovetoknow.com/home/antiques-collectibles/how-much-are-my-collectibles-worth"
          target="_blank"
          >How Much Are My Collectibles Worth? Tips for Finding Values
          (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-9420 mb-requirement-id-9424">
        (d) Explain how your collection is graded for value, physical defects,
        size, and age. Show the various classifications or ratings used in your
        collection. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://stonehards.com/articles/understanding-museum-quality-in-collectibles/"
          target="_blank"
          >Understanding Museum Quality in Collectibles and Artifacts
          (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-9420 mb-requirement-id-9425">
        (e) List the national, state, or local association(s) related to or
        associated with your collection. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://acna.us/national.html" target="_blank"
          >Antiques &amp; Collectibles National Association Directory
          (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-9420 mb-requirement-id-9426">
        (f) Explain to your counselor the purpose of and reason for the
        identification number (if applicable), series, brand name (if any), and
        any other special identification marks.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-9429">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 6. </span>
      Discuss with your counselor the plans you have to continue with the
      collection in the future.
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-9431">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 7. </span>
      Find out about career opportunities in collecting. Pick one and find out
      the education, training, and experience required for this profession.
      Discuss this with your counselor, and explain why this profession might
      interest you. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/zLYjrT_jvY0?si=p78dVOqsf4ntE4yz" target="_blank"
        >Curators, Conservators, and Museum Workers Career Video (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/bvMjvg23mBk?si=zAYSwNmi7tMyZeqV" target="_blank"
        >Dream Jobs: Antiquer (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
